# {{ .name }}

ASP.NET Minimal API sample that publishes a message with Dapr pub/sub and receives it through a subscribed endpoint.

## Run

```bash
dapr run \
  --app-id {{ .appId }} \
  --app-port 5000 \
  --dapr-http-port 3500 \
  --resources-path ./local/dapr-components \
  -- dotnet run --project ./src --urls http://localhost:5000
```

## Endpoints

- `POST /publish` - accepts `{ "text": "..." }` and publishes to Dapr pub/sub component `pubsub`, topic `messages`.
- `POST /messages` - subscribed to `pubsub/messages`; Dapr invokes this endpoint for each message.
- `GET /dapr/subscribe` - generated by Dapr.AspNetCore to expose subscriptions to the Dapr sidecar.

Use `src/{{ .name }}.http` to send a sample request.
